              â”‚       â””â”€â”€ updates.md    # Progress tracking
              â””â”€â”€ done/                 # Completed tasks
              ```

         b) Project Memory:
            - Location: /docs/
            - Purpose: Long-term project knowledge
            - Updates: Major decisions and milestones
            - Components: Architecture, decisions, standards

         c) Documentation Memory:
            - Location: /docs/templates/
            - Purpose: Standards and patterns
            - Review: Monthly template updates
            - Maintenance: Keep examples current

      2. Project Plan Document (project-plan.md):
         a) Structure:
            - Brief current status section (minimal details)
            - Chronological list of phases (from first to current)
            - Each phase with status indicator (âœ…, ğŸŸ¡, â³, etc.)
            - NO redundant sections at top and bottom
            - NO detailed implementation steps (link to phase docs instead)

         b) Content Guidelines:
            - Concise summaries only (<3 sentences per phase)
            - Links to comprehensive phase documentation
            - Latest update timestamp at document top
            - Critical path dependencies between phases
            - AVOID duplicating information from phase documents
            - Focus on progression and relationships between phases

         c) Maintenance:
            - Update only current phase status
            - Archive completed phases to minimal summaries
            - Move detailed information to phase documents
            - Update timestamp with every change

      3. Task Documentation Files:
         a) plan.md Requirements:
            - Problem Analysis
            - Solution Design
            - Implementation Steps
            - Affected Components
            - Testing Plan
            - Documentation Impact
            - Dependencies

         b) updates.md Structure:
            - Current Status (top, single entry)
            - Progress History (chronological)
            - Decisions Log
            - Issues Encountered
            - Next Steps

         c) summary.md Structure:
            - Overview of completed phase
            - Key achievements and outcomes
            - Technical approach summary
            - Benefits realized
            - Lessons learned
            - Related documentation links

      4. Status Update Process:
         a) Current Status:
            - Single active status
            - Use `date "+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M"` for timestamps
            - Previous status moves to history

         b) Progress Markers:
            - âœ“ Completed work
            - ğŸ¤” Decisions made
            - âŒ Issues encountered
            - â­ï¸ Next steps
            - ğŸ“š Documentation updates

      5. File Management:
         a) Active Tasks:
            - Keep in /docs/working-memory/open/
            - Regular updates to plan.md and updates.md
            - Move to /done/ when complete

         b) Templates:
            - Use task-plan-template.md
            - Use task-updates-template.md
            - Follow standard formats

         c) Maintenance:
            - Weekly active task review
            - Monthly completed task archival
            - Clean directory structure

      6. Cross-Referencing:
         a) Internal Links:
            - Between plan.md and updates.md
            - Task ID in all updates
            - Component and task relationships

         b) External Links:
            - Related documentation
            - Affected components
            - External dependencies

      7. Version Control:
         a) Commit Patterns:
            - Prefix: docs(memory)
            - Include task ID
            - Reference memory types

         b) Branch Management:
            - Format: docs/memory/{task-id}
            - Short-lived, task-specific
            - Merge after completion

         c) Version Tagging:
            - Format: memory/{YYYY-MM}
            - Monthly snapshots
            - Archive old memory

      Remember:
      - Update status before starting work
      - Document decisions immediately
      - Keep progress log current
      - Use proper timestamps
      - Regular maintenance and cleanup
      - Keep project-plan.md concise and chronological
